## 🗄️ Database Design Highlights
The system utilizes a flat, high-performance Firestore layout consisting of two main collections linked by a logical relationship:

### 1. `users` Collection
Stores metadata for student and coordinator profiles.
* **Document ID**: Firebase Auth `uid`
```json
{
  "role": "student", // "student" or "admin"
  "studentId": "2021-04567",
  "firstName": "Juan",
  "lastName": "Dela Cruz",
  "section": "BSIT-4A",
  "email": "juan@student.com",
  "company": "ABC Corp",
  "position": "IT Intern",
  "ojtStart": "2026-01-05", // Sets calculations base
  "workSchedule": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5], // Monday (1) to Friday (5)
  "isActive": true,
  "createdAt": "Timestamp"
}
```

### 2. `journals` Collection
Stores the daily records submitted by interns.
* **Document ID**: `${userId}_${date}` (e.g., `ltfU9DKVUaF5PuBQm0Mx_2026-02-13`)
  > [!NOTE]
  > Using a composite ID of `${userId}_${date}` naturally enforces database-level uniqueness. It is structurally impossible for a student to create more than one journal for the same day.

```json
{
  "userId": "ltfU9DKVUaF5PuBQm0Mx",
  "date": "2026-02-13",
  "week": 6, // Calculated dynamically
  "content": "Worked on backend validation checks and integrated Cloud Firestore.",
  "submitted": true,
  "reviewed": false,
  "remarks": "",
  "timestamp": "Timestamp", // Server-side creation time
  "updatedAt": "Timestamp"
}
```

